Job Description:
JOB PURPOSE
The successful post holder will fully meet and exceed the student recruitment targets of the school, including Summer School recruitment targets and provide excellent quality, professional customer service to prospective and current parents of the school.
Responsibilities and Duties:
• Meet and exceed the school’s student recruitment targets by effectively converting prospective parents’ enquiries into enrollments;
• Proactively follow up on all enquiries to ensure prospective parents receive excellent customer service and proceed with their applications and enrollment;
• Provide well-tailored tours and advisory consultations to prospective parents, emphasizing the school’s strengths and persuasively convincing them the school is the best choice for their child;
• Timely and professionally process all admissions related documentation, from student application, testing and confirmation letters and entering all data on ISAMS;
• Inform all relevant teachers of any new enrolments, providing student profiles and key documentation to them prior to the student’s arrival so that teachers are well prepared and to issue ID cards;
• Assist Admissions Supervisor with producing regular Admissions reports and with reviewing and updating the current and prospective parents’ database;
• Assist Admissions Supervisor with reviewing student recruitment performance, and with developing and implementing effective student recruitment plans for the school;
• Administer admissions tests and to schedule admissions interviews as appropriate for the applicant’s age group and background;
• Record, update and review all enquiries, tests, visits and applications, and receive and record any student withdrawal forms for the school’s current students;
• Continuously monitor parent feedback and identify shifts in parent perceptions and preferences, reporting them to Admissions Supervisor on a regular basis;
• Regularly visit the school’s key competitors websites to keep the team updated on any new competitor developments, proposing actions to counteract them;
• Provide excellent customer service to the school’s students, parents and prospective families, projecting professional image of the school and ensuring their full satisfaction;
• Identify potential new feeders and propose new partnerships to Admissions Supervisor;
• Assist Admissions Supervisor with administrative duties;
• Support school events and whole-school activities as required and work very closely with the school’s Marketing & Communications team;
• Follow all Admissions policies and procedures and process related paperwork as agreed with the Admissions Supervisor;
• Perform any other duties assigned by the Admissions Supervisor or Head of School, or their designate, after due consultation.

